The paper discusses the Lottery Ticket Hypothesis, which is a concept in deep learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on finding sub-networks that perform better than their original counterparts, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed algorithm also involves gradient-based methods, which are commonly used in neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
